.TH "gpiochip_irq_map" 9 "gpiochip_irq_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiochip_irq_map \- maps an IRQ into a GPIO irqchip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiochip_irq_map
.BI "(struct irq_domain *d "  ","
.BI "unsigned int irq "  ","
.BI "irq_hw_number_t hwirq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "d" 12
the irqdomain used by this irqchip
.IP "irq" 12
the global irq number used by this GPIO irqchip irq
.IP "hwirq" 12
the local IRQ/GPIO line offset on this gpiochip
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will set up the mapping for a certain IRQ line on a
gpiochip by assigning the gpiochip as chip data, and using the irqchip
stored inside the gpiochip.
